    <sect2>
        <title>1.Requirements</title>
        <para>Before you start, you need:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>A Linux system</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Some knowledge about Linux</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Some knowledger about XML</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Some knowledge about the console</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </sect2>
    <sect3>
        <title>2.Install Daps</title>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>1. Open Yast</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>2. Click on Software Management</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>3. Go to Search</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>4. Search for "daps"</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>5. Install "daps" and "daps-docmanager</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </sect3>
    <sect4>
        <title>3.Transform</title>
        <para> If you want to transform .xml to .pdf for example then use this way to do
            this:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>1. Open your console with Alt+F2. Type into this line: console.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>2. Enter in your console: "daps -e YOUR_XML_FILE pdf".</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>3. Finished. Your .xml file is now a .pdf file.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para> if you want a other format, change the word text into txt, epub, wiki or man. More
        options can you see with the command: "daps --help"</para>
    </sect4>
